thread.title_full: Fog shrouds Cathedral Park and St Johns Bridge (photos) | OregonLive.com

author: Mike Zacchino | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Fog shrouds Cathedral Park and St Johns Bridge (photos)
text:
Fog hung over Cathedral Park and the St Johns bridge this morning, lingering a bit longer than in other parts of Portland. We can expect to see patches of fog on Thursday and Friday this week as well.
The low level of the Willamette River has exposed pilings once used for the ferry terminal between St Johns and Linnton under the St Johns Bridge in Cathedral Park.
